title: NCCU shifts start time for Saturday game
text:
NCCU shifts start time for Saturday game 
Posted 12:17 p.m. today Your friends e-mail addresses (comma separated): * Subject: * Are you human? * You must enter the characters with black color that stand out from the other characters 
Durham, N.C. — Due to the forecast of inclement weather, the North Carolina Central University football game versus Bethune-Cookman University on Saturday, Oct. 3 in O’Kelly-Riddick Stadium has been changed from 4 p.m. to a 2 p.m. kickoff. 
The Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference match-up can be seen live on ESPN3 and tape delayed on ESPNU at 10:30 on Saturday night.
